# Resize Handling

## Size Detection

Use `GetConsoleScreenBufferInfo` on stdout handle directly — never `$Host.UI.RawUI.WindowSize` or `[Console]::WindowWidth` (return stale values in polling loops).

```powershell
$csbi = New-Object $script:CSBIType
$hOut = $script:MouseAPI::GetStdHandle(-11)
if ($script:MouseAPI::GetConsoleScreenBufferInfo($hOut, [ref]$csbi)) {
    $w = [int]($csbi.srWindow.Right  - $csbi.srWindow.Left + 1)
    $h = [int]($csbi.srWindow.Bottom - $csbi.srWindow.Top + 1)
}
```

## Invoke-ResizeHandler Flow

1. Reset quote and locked height
2. Draw resize logo (or clear in hidden mode)
3. 1ms poll loop: detect size change, redraw, artifact cleanup every 50 draws
4. Stability: elapsed >= 100ms AND LMB not held -> exit
5. `Restore-ConsoleInputMode` + `Send-ConsoleWakeKey` + return `$pendingSize`
6. Does NOT clear screen on exit — caller's `Flush-Buffer -ClearFirst` replaces the logo

## Dialog Resize Pattern

```
Invoke-ResizeHandler -> update HostWidth/HostHeight
-> Write-MainFrame -Force -NoFlush
-> & $ParentRedrawCallback (if sub-dialog)
-> queue dialog redraw
-> Flush-Buffer -ClearFirst (single atomic paint)
```

## $oldWindowSize Sync

Both `$oldWindowSize` and `$OldBufferSize` must be synced at every dialog exit path to prevent false resize detection on the next main loop iteration.
